    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>ROI Align</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Another major contribution of Mask R-CNN is the refinement of the ROI pooling. In ROI, the warping is digitalized (top left diagram below): the cell boundaries of the target feature map are forced to realign with the boundary of the input feature maps. Therefore, each target cells may not be in the same size (bottom left diagram). Mask R-CNN uses <strong>ROI Align </strong>which does not digitalize the boundary of the cells (top right) and make every target cell to have the same size (bottom right). It also applies interpolation to calculate the feature map values within the cell better. For example, by applying interpolation, the maximum feature value on the top left is changed from 0.8 to 0.88 now.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
